  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nAt some point it may happen that when user sends transaction it is displayed as Pending and has hash in transaction history, however, it never appears in Pending state in the actual network (can't find in Etherscan), even if Gas Price was twice more than current recommended.\nIt reproducible when for the same account changing network back and forth (not app restart but re-login).\nBut could not reproduce when re-login being in the same network.   \n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nTransaction sent and mined as expected disregard how many times network changed for account \n\n#### Actual behavior\n\nTX never found in the Etherscan and never mined if I change the the network for the same account multiple times\n![2020_11_24_19_32_40_trim (1)](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/100131808-3175c400-2e8d-11eb-9111-5da0d1b995b8.gif)\n\n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n1) Open Status and recover an account with funds in Mainnet and Rinkeby\n2) Switch network to Rinkeby\n3) Send transaction (ETHri) in Rinkeby network to any address. No need to wait till it is mined.\n4) Switch network back to Mainnet\n5) Send ETH transaction\n6) Check the transaction from 5th step if it's ever appear in Etherscan as Pending/Success\n**Actual result:** No transaction appears in Etherscan however, it's `Pending...` in Status.\n\nNote: if it's OK in 6th step, - repeat 2-5th steps once more\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: release 1.8\n- Operating System: Android and iOS\n\n#### Logs\n\n[geth.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/5591494/geth.log)\n[Status.log](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/5591496/Status.log)",
